== Intent ==

[[web programming]] with [[Language:HTML5]]

== Languages ==

* [[Language:HTML5]]
* [[Language:JavaScript]]

== Technologies ==

* [[Technology:B-Tree|B-Tree]]-based indexed database

== Features ==

* [[101feature:Company]]
* [[101feature:Total]]
* [[101feature:Cut]]

== Motivation ==

The indexed database is the current alternative to the (deprecated) [[101implementation:html5sqlDatabase|web database]] in HTML5. Apart from web storage ([[101implementation:html5local|local storage]] and [[101implementation:html5session|session storage]]), the indexed database feature gains the main support in relation to [[offline storage]].

== Illustration ==

<syntaxhighlight lang="javascript">
companies.indexedDB.cut = function() {
	// get database
	var db = companies.indexedDB.db;

	// create transaction to the indexed database
	var transEmp = db.transaction(["Employee"], IDBTransaction.READ_WRITE, 0);
	// retrieve employee store
	var empStore = transEmp.objectStore("Employee");
	
	// Get every single employee in the store
	var keyRange = IDBKeyRange.lowerBound(0);
	var cursorRequest = empStore.openCursor(keyRange);

	// cursor runs through the result-set
	cursorRequest.onsuccess = function(e) {
		var result = e.target.result;
		if(!!result == false)
			return;

		// cut the salary
		result.value.salary = result.value.salary / 2;
		// store the employee
		empStore.put(result.value);
		// return to top
		result.continue();
	};
	
	cursorRequest.onerror = companies.indexedDB.onerror;
}
</syntaxhighlight>

== Usage ==

* Open the 101companies.html with your web-browser (check [[Language:HTML5|HTML5]] for the HTML5-support of your browser)

